<Content>Hong Kong's finest Having stayed at the 4 seasons several times (including my wedding night!), this is without doubt my fav hotel in HK. The place is still gleaming, as the hotel only opened in late 2005. The 4 seasons is based on a sleek contemporary design, as opposed to the Peninsula鈥檚 old world grandeur. The rooms are spacious, with a huge bathrooms and good showers. Also great complimentary toiletries by L'Occitane - always a sign of a good hotel. No cheap soap here!Situated within the IFC mall complex, the 4 seasons is easy to get to from the Central airport express station, which is just a 10 minute walk away through the mall. We normally use the free car drop-off service on our return to the airport express terminal.Highlights:- Fantastic roof-top outdoor pool with one of the world's most spectacular views across HK harbour.- Contemporary (free) Jacuzzi, steam room and Spa, which never seems to be too busy and is a great place to unwind. Feels like you are in a proper spa, rather than a hotel.- Well appointed, large rooms with great views and facilities. - Excellent service from all staff, who have been trained to the highest degree. Unlike some 5* hotels, the atmosphere is not stuffy.Criticisms (I am nit-picking here):- Being in the heart of Central, the 4 seasons is less well located for visiting Wan Chai (which has a huge selection of places to eat). The Central area is a bit dead at night. The Star Ferry terminal is located close by, making access to Kowloon easy.- I do find the decor in the Chinese styled rooms a little over-the-top and cluttered. Maybe im more of a minimalist.- There is often a strong smell of Cigar smoke when entering the foyer in the evening, as the main bar is open to the foyer. Aside from putting up a wall, im not sure what can be done? Being a non-smoker, I do find this a bit unpleasant.Overall, a great place to stay and one i will definately seek out on my next trip to HK. 
