<Content>A beautiful hotel, with first rate service and facilities Our experience at the Four Seasons in Hong Kong was excellent all round. The hotel has a great location in the new International Finance Centre (IFC), so its easy to access Central and the ferry piers. The building itself is fabulous to look at, and is decorated in a stylish minimalist way, whilst remaining comfortable and pleasant.Although I guess its primarily designed for business people, we found it to be an ideal base for our family (two young childen). In particular, the infinity swimming pools are superb, and provide a good place for RR after a day of sight-seeing or shopping.The restaurants in the hotel are of top quality, but a bit formal for families. However, there is obviously no shortage of restaurants in the surrounding area or in the IFC mall below.On the other hand, breakfast, in the 45th floor buisness centre, was very good, and felt quite relaxed.Our room was beautiful (the kids didn't want to leave it!). We had two double beds and a lovely bathroom, and a panormaic view of the harbour. Broadband, LCD TVs, in-room facilities all on tap.The Four Seasons in Hong Kong is undoubtedly one of the best hotels we have stayed in - very highly recommended. 
