<Content>The Four Seasons an excellent hotel! What to say about the 4Seasons Hotel?In the hotel, the only trouble was to find the room card, to insert once inside the lift, to go to the room floor.Excellent service at the reception desk and good recommendations on what to do and what to see in HK.Good size rooms, with plasma, dvd..Absolutely super bathroom.We book 2 roooms (1 with view on the port and 1 with view on city). THe room with view on the city was biiger and still offeredgreat view over HK city, and was 20% cheaper.A -must to be see- in the hotel, is the swimming pool and the spa, both located in the 6 th floor.Swimming pool is just too great !!!. Spa was very convenient as well,to have shower before leaving HK at 8pm.Hotel is very convenient. Located just next to IFC mall, and 2 minutes walk from the Airport Express connection to get you to airport (time for connection: 25 minutes and price 13$).Hotel provide very convenient and free shuttle to AirportExpress terminal, so to take the connection to the airport.What to see in HK:-Get the cable car to top of mountain and get a great view over HK city (best views at sunset)-DISNEY park (directly with subway). Disney park is 1 year oldand has all. 3-D Disney movie and LION KING show were the best.-Go to STANLEY village (directly with bus 260), Stanley is a touristic village, outside HK, but the scenery on the way to the village is just too great.. Allow 2-3 hours for excursion.Restaurants tips in HK:-Go to top floor restaurant FELIX at PENINSULA HOTEL.Restaurant is not cheap, but great service and food (fusion). Super views over HK city.Take ferry to go back to Foiur Seasons hotel.-Chinese restaurantDirectly in the IFC mall (top fllor) , 2 minutes walk from hotel,go to the excellent chinese restaurant LEI GARDEN. LEI GARDEN is not cheap but provides excellent food, and excellent service. Reservations recommended 2295 0238-Japanese restaurant:KANAZAWA restaurant, tel 2895 0818, 48 Percival st, 2nd floorSmall bu