<Content>Fabulous! My first time in Hong Kong was made all the better by staying in the Four Seasons. If you can, organise for the hotel pick up from HK airport (KHD 800 each way). We were met at the plane, whisked on a buggy to customs, then straight down to luggage and into air-conditioned limo. On arrival at the hotel, we were greeted by name at our car and taken directly to our room where we were checked in in comfort - and this was all within 1 hour of landing!My boyfriend loved the 42 plasma screen opposite the bed and it came in use when the jet-lag kicked in! The bed itself was also huge and incredibly comfortable.We had a city view which, at night, was fabulous with all the lights and we didn't feel cheated by not having a harbour view.The Spa/Pool was amazing. There is an outdoor infinity pool which overlooks the harbour and the hot tub (on what was a really chilly morning) was most welcome.I have stayed in many Four Seasons hotels and this is definitely one of the best. Overall the service was excellent and unobtrusive. Definitely a great city hotel which I would thoroughly recommend to tourists/business travellers. 
