<Content>You have to stay there! I went to HK on business and stayed at Four Seasons. I have stayed at several in the chain and find each and everyone of them to be guaranteed luxury and service.The staff upon arrival are friendly, but not annoying or in your face. The check-in agent showed me to my room, hit the key points and left without being intrusive.The room was large with amazing features. The doors were solid, cupboards and wardrobes everywhere and 42 plasma screen! The bathroom was amzing, large and TV screen above the bath.Location is in the IFC mall, which was handy as my office is in IFC 2 and all the shops you could possibly want were there. Nearby was the rain to the airport. It also wasn't a long walk on the walkways into the cityI visited the pool and spa before getting my midnight flight. The pool was amazing, infinity edge and overlooking the city lights, particularly at Christmas time was wonderful. Inside the hot tub was brilliant and the attendant was very attentive.I had room service a couple of nights and the food was above average.Overall, fantastic hotel, especially for business. 
